String 
Sequence of character , refers to a series of characters enclosed within double quotes. String can also be treated as object in java. String can also be 
treated as array of character.

Types of String 
a.mutable - which can be modified even after creation. we can create mutable string by using string buffer or string builder class.
e.g -> StringBuilder,StringBuffer

b.immutable - such string which cannot be modified after creation. 
e.g ->String 

Different ways to compare two Strings
1.==
2. equals()
3.equalIgnoreCase()
4. compareTo


*when we concate two string using concate method , the resuting string will get memory on non-constant pool, + operator can also be used to concate two strings.
 we use  the "+" operator along with string references , the resultant string will get memory on the non-constant code. However if we use plus operator along with raw string/data 
 the resultant string will get memory on the constant port. 


The intern method takes  a copy of the string present on the non-constant pool and move it to the constant pool.

CompareTo - compares two string character by character. It would return positive value if the first string is greater, it is going to return a negative value
if the second string is greater, it will return zero if both the strings are equal . It compares character based on their unicode value;

Inbuilt Method in String


Initial capacity of stringBuffer and StringBuilder is 16 , however if we exceed this capacity ,the striingBuffer or StringBuiulder will increase its capacity by
 using the formula - > new capacity = old capacity * 2 +2;
 Although the default initial capacity of a StringBuffer and StringBuilder is 16 we as a programmer can define(set) our own initial capacity.  

Difference between String Buffer and String Builder
String builder is not a thread safe class.


