Flow of java Program
As soon as method is called in java, its activation record is created on the stack segment.Activation record refers to a chunk of memory allocated on the 
stack segment for the execution of a method. Activation record is also known as stack frame. All the variable which are created inside the body of a method are 
allocated memory on the activation record of particular method. As soon as control reaches the end of the method, it returns to where it came from.
As soon as control exits a method , its activation record gets deleted. When an activation record is deleted , all the variable present on that activation record 
are also deleted. On the heap segment if there are such object to whom no one is refering to , this objects are also known as anonymous, orphan or garbage object.
Such objects will be collected by the garbage collector thread. 
In the above programs , the add method does not accept any value and does not return any value from caller of method , hence it is called no input- no output.


Instance variable vs local variable
1. Instance variable are defined inside the class but outside the method of class , local variables are defined inside a method of class.
2.Instance variable are alloted memory when object is created, local variable are assigned the memory when the method is called.
3.Instance variable are alloted memory inside the object on the heap segment, local variable are assigned on the activation record of the specific method of the 
stack segment.
4.Instance variable are deleted when the object is deleted , local variables are deleted when control exits the method and respective activation record is deleted.

