Method Overloading

In the previous program , all the methods are performing same task of addition, however while calling this method one must remember the specific method name
based on there requirement . The process of remembering so many names can be hectic , to avoid this problem in java, Java uses the concept of method overloading.
Method overloading is a concept in which multiple methods of the same class have the same name but vary in their signature. The biggest advantage of method overloading
 is that using a same method name , we can perform different operation.Method Overloading clearly eases the usability of code. 
 Method Overloading is also known as compile time polymorphism. This is because during the compile time only, it is decided which method has to be called.
 Since multiple methods are having the same name and ambiguity problem arises , to overcome this problem the compiler uses the following rules.
 1. the compiler is going to match the number of arguements. 
 2.if there are multiple methods with same name and same number of arguements, the compiler will now match the data types of arguements.
 3.If even after following the above two rule, if confusion is still there, now compiler will compare the order of data type
 
 If Method overloading has to exists , one or more of the above rules must be satisfied. It is also known as virtual or false polymorphism.
 
 For true polymorphism to exists , one isto many relationship should exists. But in method overloading , one isto many relationship does not exists. In the above 
 example , it appears as single  add method is doing multiple tasks but in reality multiple add methods are doing one tasks each. It is an examle of false polymorphism and 
 not true polymorphism. 
 
