 2.Can we overload main method?


Encapsulation - is a paradigm of object oriented programming system which enables us to provide security to the important dat member of a class. In encapsulation 
for providing security to the important data member, we declare the data members as private . The private member are accessible from within the same class,private
prevents complete access but encapsulation does not prevent complete access rather it provides control access. Control access is provided using public setter and
public getter. This setter and getter method must contain validation code in order to provide controlled access. Since setter and getter are public, they can be 
accessed from even outside the class. Also since this setter and getter method are present within the same class as the private member they can access the private 
members. 


Constructor 

What is Shadowing problem?
According to industry standard, inside a setter method the name of a local variable must be same as the name of instance variable but when we do 
this modification of values, it is not reflected in the instance variable. This is because the JVM is not able to differentiate between the local 
variable and the instance variable. As a result all the modification are basically happening on the local variable themselves. It appears that 
the local variables are shadowing the instance variable and hence the above problem is also knows as Shadowing problem. 

